<#GAPDoc Label="ChapQuiverUtilitiesOverquiver">
<Section>
  <Heading>
    Introduction
  </Heading>

  My discrete model of a SB algebra uses quivers. In particular, from a SB algebra <M>A</M>, it creates a <M>1</M>-regular quiver called the <E>overquiver of <M>A</M></E>. The &SBStrips; package includes several tools for working with the overquiver of an algebra, along with other utility functions for use on <M>1</M>-regular or special biserial quivers. (The latter might also be called <E>sub-<M>2</M>-regular</E>.)
</Section>

